# MAAC OpenAPI
This is a technical document. For marketing or customer service colleagues, please refer to [operating manual](https://pse.is/3r8rd6).<br>
If you have any questions, please contact [customer-supoort@cresclab.com](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com).<br><br>

查看中文版文件請至 [MAAC Open API](https://cresclab.docs.apiary.io/)<br>

## Purpose
---
Use MAAC's official account to connect with MAAC OpenAPI to access contact information, add tags, add audiences, push messages and other functions.
It can be connected to third-party platforms to marketing automation and CRM data connection.

## Considerations

- Do not use `http` when connecting with API, please use `https` to avoid insecure data transmission.
- In a production environment, please use `https://api.cresclab.com`, and the connection must be Server-to-server data connection.
- If you are using MAAC in the Japan region, please use `https://api.jp.cresclab.com`

## API Description
---
### Format
MAAC OpenAPI uses REST API format, JSON format, and UTF-8 encoding.

### Request header
Bring the Authorization parameter in the HTTP header to call MAAC OpenAPI
| Request header | Description |
| :-- | :-- |
|Authorization| Bearer `{Access token}` |

<a name="rate_limits"></a>
### Rate limits

#### MAAC Rate limit
MAAC server applies the following rate limits for each endpoint based on official accounts.
The detailed API limits are listed in the table below.
| API                                      | rate limiting |
| :--------------------------------------- | :------------ |
| import contacts                          | 15/m          |
| send push message                        | 170/s         |
| send multicast message                   | 10/s          |
| send enhanced multicast                  | 170/s         |
| send SMS+ message                        | 170/s         |
| send multicast SMS+ message              | 10/s          |

<a name="line_rate_limits"></a>
#### Line Rate limit
Line server applies the following rate limits for each endpoint based on official accounts.
These API calls are counted toward the total usage across all purposes, including MAAC products (such as broadcasts) and other integrations.
The detailed API limits are listed in the table below.
| API                                      | rate limiting |
| :--------------------------------------- | :------------ |
| send push message                        | 2000/s        |
| send multicast message                   | 200/s        |


### status codes
| code | description                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
| :--- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
|200| `OK` - Request successful (The response status code is 201 when part of the resource creation API request is successful)                                                                                                   |
|201| `Created` - The request has been fulfilled and has resulted in one or more new resources being created.                                                                                                                    |
|204| `No Content` - The server has successfully fulfilled the request and that there is no additional content to send in the response payload body.                                                                             |
|400| `Bad Request` - The server cannot or will not process the request due to something that is perceived to be a client error (e.g., malformed request syntax, invalid request message framing, or deceptive request routing). |
|401| `Unauthorized` - The request has not been applied because it lacks valid authentication credentials for the target resource.                                                                                               |
|403| `Forbidden` - the server understood the request but refuses to authorize it.                                                                                                                                               |
|404| `Not Found` - The origin server did not find a current representation for the target resource or is not willing to disclose that one exists.                                                                               |
|405| `Method Not Allowed` - The method received in the request-line is known by the origin server but not supported by the target resource.                                                                                     |
|429| `Too Many Requests` - Possible reasons for this error include exceeding [the rate limit](#rate_limits) for each bot, or the system experiencing high traffic during peak hours. We recommend trying again after a few seconds, and extending the interval between each request to reduce the request frequency and help the system handle your requests more efficiently. |

## Webhook

---

### Overview

When the relevant events you subscribe to occur, MAAC will actively notify your system through Webhooks to achieve real-time synchronization of information.

### Webhook Headers

- `CrescLab-Idempotency-Key` to identify unique webhooks.
- `CrescLab-Signature` to verify the events were sent by MAAC.

### Considerations

- We recommend processing events asynchronously, so that processing an HTTP POST request doesn't cause delays in processing subsequent requests.
- Your server may receive malicious HTTP POST requests that weren't sent from the MAAC Platform.
Don't process any webhook event objects until you have verified their signatures.
- You need to ensure the stability of your own connection and flow control. We provide retry services but do not help save all log records.

### Response

Your server must return [status code 200](https://developer.mozilla.org/zh-TW/docs/Web/HTTP/Status/200) after it receives the HTTP POST request sent from the MAAC Platform.

### Retry policy

If a webhook POST to a server receives the following responses indicate transient problems will retry:

- HTTP 408, 429, and 5xx response codes.
- Socket timeouts and TCP disconnects.

We perform retry requests with an exponential backoff algorithm by increasing the waiting time between retries up to a maximum backoff time.
MAAC will retry as following steps:

1. Make a request to Webhook endpoint .
2. If the request fails, wait 1 second and retry the request.
3. If the request fails, wait 2 seconds and retry the request.
4. If the request fails, wait 4 seconds and retry the request.

You can detect duplicate webhook events by comparing the `CrescLab-Idempotency-Key` header to previous events.

### Check the webhook signatures

MAAC signs the webhook events using HMAC-SHA256 and hex digest encoding by including a signature in each event's `CrescLab-Signature` header.
This allows you to verify that the events were sent by MAAC, not by a third party.
We provide the following Python snippet as a reference implementation.

Before you can verify signatures, you need to retrieve your endpoint's secret from your [Dashboard's Webhooks settings](https://maac.cresclab.com/webhooks).
MAAC generates a unique secret key for each endpoint. Select an endpoint that you want to obtain the secret for, then click the eye icon button to reveal the secret.

The following is an example of how to implement signature validation in Python®.

```python
import hashlib
import hmac

# Please use row string `r"..."` to present body.
# if you don't use raw string, you need to escape the backslash to present unicode. E.g: do not use `\u65b0`, instead, use escape `\\u65b0`
# In json string, please keep the space after comma and colon. E.g: do not remove spaces {"a":1,"b":2}, instead, keep spaces {"a": 1,"b": 2}

share_secret = "..."  # share secret string
header_signature = "..."  # CrescLab-Signature in request header
body = r"..."  # Request body string (python's raw string)
signature = hmac.new(
    share_secret.encode("utf-8"), body.encode("utf-8"), hashlib.sha256
).hexdigest()
assert hmac.compare_digest(signature, header_signature)
```

## FAQ
---
> #### How to enable OpenAPI?
> If you have activated MAAC but not yet enabled OpenAPI, please contact [Customer support](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com)

> #### How to get Access token?
> If you have activated MAAC and enabled OpenAPI, you can generate an Access token in [MAAC](https://maac.cresclab.com) : API> API token> click the "Get Token" button.
![Schematic](https://storage.googleapis.com/maac-media/maac/sample/OpenAPI%20issue%20token.png)


> #### What if the Access token is lost?
> Click "Generate Token" and save it yourself to start using Open API. If it is missing, please generate it again. If you need to delete the Token for security, please contact the partner of the crescendo lab.

> #### Does the access token expired?
> The period of use is the contract period signed by the crescendo lab and the partner

> #### Pricing?
> Please refer to the sales deck. There are four major categories, and each category can correspond to the itemized API of this file. The detailed pricing rules are based on your official account purchase plan, please contact us for details [Customer support](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com)。

