# Group Contact
|column | type | description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
|line_uid| String | The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
|line_display_name| String | The name defined by the contact in the official LINE account with maximum 255 characters
|display_name| String | The name showed in MAAC with maximum 255 characters
|email| String | Contact email address
|mobile| String | Contact phone number
|customer_id| String | User ID of the third-party system
|gender| String | Contact gender (default is predicted by MAAC AI)<br>`male` :male<br>`female`：female<br>`unknown`：unknown
|birthday| String | Contact birthday (ISO Format)
|tags| Array[String] | All valid MAAC tags
|status| String | Contact status <br>`follow` : Contacts of LINE official account<br>`auth` : The contacts have authorized the LINE official account to get their information<br>`unfollow` : The contacts have blocked the official account
|updated_at| String | Contact information update time
|created_at| String | Contact creation time
|blocked_at| String | The time when the contact blocked the official account
---

## Contact [/openapi/v1/member/]

### Get contact list [GET /openapi/v1/member/{?member_id,line_uid,email,mobile,customer_id,status,updated_at_min,updated_at_max,all_tag,start}]
Get a list of the information of contacts belonging to the official account in MAAC. The list is paged for every 300 contact information.

* Query Parameter can be used to filter eligible contacts
* Query parameters containing special characters or symbols should be encoded
* Bring the token in the response `next` parameter of the previous page into the `start` parameter of the request to get the next page.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + line_uid : `Uoooxxxoooxxxoooxxxoooxxxoooxx` (optional, string)
    + member_id : `20240429` (optional, int)
    + email : `demo@cresclab.com` (optional, string)
    + mobile : `%2b886912345678` (optional, string) -
    the **"+"** symbols should be encoded as **"%2b"**<br>
    + customer_id : `1235734897` (optional, string)
    + status : `follow` (optional, string)
    + updated_at_min : `2017-05-17` (optional, string) ... Filter contacts who have updated information after this date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**
    + updated_at_max :  `2020-05-17` (optional, string) ... Filter contacts who have updated information before this date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**
    + all_tag = 0 (optional, number) ... **0**: Use the above two parameters to filter the time when contacts are tagged<br> **1**: Get all tags of contacts<br>
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string)-
    The id of the next page will be returned to the `next` parameter of the previous page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - contact data array
            + (object)
                + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
                + `line_display_name` (string) - The name defined by the contact in the official LINE account with maximum 255 characters
                + `display_name` (string) - The name showed in MAAC with maximum 255 characters
                + `email` (string) - Contact email
                + `mobile` (string) - Contact phone number
                + `customer_id` (string) - User ID of the third-party system
                + `gender` (string) - Contact gender
                + `birthday` (string) - Contact birthday (ISO Format)
                + `tags` (array) - Array of all valid tags
                    + (string) - Tag name
                + `tags_detail` (array) - Array of tags detail
                    + (object)
                        + `name` (string) - Tag name
                        + `tagged_at` (string) - The timestamp when the tag is first time tagged to this contact
                + `status` (string) - Contact status
                + `updated_at` (string) - Contact information update time
                + `created_at` (string) - Contact creation time
                + `blocked_at` (string) - The time when the contact blocked the official account
        + `next` (string) - page token of the next page

    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    {
                        "line_uid": "U353dc4b8ea88acaa8663c6cd9a4f4000",
                        "line_display_name": "Alan Mathison Turing",
                        "display_name": "Alan Mathison Turing",
                        "email": "alan@example.com",
                        "mobile": "+886987654321",
                        "customer_id": "1235734897",
                        "gender": "male",
                        "birthday": "2017-05-17",
                        "tags": [
                            "tag1"
                        ],
                        "tags_detail": [
                            {
                                "name": "tag1",
                                "tagged_at": "2020-01-13T18:58:21.604283+08:00"
                            }
                        ],
                        "status": "follow",
                        "updated_at": "2020-01-13T18:58:21.604283+08:00",
                        "created_at": "2020-01-13T18:48:23.604283+08:00",
                        "blocked_at": "2020-01-13T18:48:23.604283+08:00"
                    }
                ],
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D"
            }

### Update contact [PATCH /openapi/v1/member/{line_uid}/]
Update your contact information in MAAC.
- Bind contacts by mapping customer_id and update the contact information in MAAC.
- Unbind contacts by depositing `null` to `customer_id`.

+ Parameters
    + line_uid (required, string, `U21d78de43c3ce40fbcbc5c4ce6dfe0b0`)

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `display_name` (optional, string) - The name showed in MAAC
        + `customer_id` (optional, string) - User ID of the third-party system
        + `email` (optional, string) - Contact email
        + `mobile` (optional, string) - Contact phone number, please use E.164 format. If the number starts with 09XX, it will be automatically converted to E.164 format according to the channel's region.
        + `gender` (optional, string) - Contact gender
          value: **male**, **female**, **unknown**
        + `birthday` (optional, string) - Contact birthday (ISO Format)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "display_name": "Alan Mathison Turing",
                "customer_id": "fake-cid",
                "email": "example@example.com",
                "mobile": "+886910123456",
                "gender": "male",
                "birthday": "2017-05-17"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
        + `line_display_name` (string) - The name defined by the contact in the official LINE account with maximum 255 characters
        + `display_name` (string) - The name showed in MAAC with maximum 255 characters
        + `email` (string) - Contact email
        + `mobile` (string) - Contact phone number
        + `customer_id` (string) - User ID of the third-party system
        + `gender` (string) - Contact gender
        + `birthday` (string) - Contact birthday (ISO Format)
        + `tags` (array) - Array of all valid tags
            + (string) - Tag name
        + `tags_detail` (array) - Array of tags detail
            + (object)
                + `name` (string) - Tag name
                + `tagged_at` (string) - The timestamp when the tag is first time tagged to this contact
        + `status` (string) - Contact status
        + `updated_at` (string) - Contact information update time
        + `created_at` (string) - Contact creation time
        + `blocked_at` (string) - The time when the contact blocked the official account

    + Body

            {
                "line_uid": "U353dc4b8ea88acaa8663c6cd9a4f4000",
                "line_display_name": "Alan Mathison Turing",
                "display_name": "Alan Mathison Turing",
                "email": "example@example.com",
                "mobile": "+886910123456",
                "customer_id": "fake-cid",
                "gender": "male",
                "birthday": "2017-05-17",
                "tags": [
                    "tag1"
                ],
                "tags_detail": [
                    {
                        "name": "tag1",
                        "tagged_at": "2020-01-13T18:58:21.604283+08:00"
                    }
                ],
                "status": "follow",
                "updated_at": "2020-01-13T18:58:21.604283+08:00",
                "created_at": "2020-01-13T18:48:23.604283+08:00",
                "blocked_at": "2020-01-13T18:48:23.604283+08:00"
            }

### Import contact [POST /openapi/v1/member/import/]

If you have an existing membership database, you can also import it through MAAC OpenAPI to integrate data.

* Import up to 10,000 contact information in a single request
* Maximum number of concurrent import task: 1 import task
* Maximum rate of import task: 15/min
* The maximum body size of a single request is 10MB
* For contacts who are successfully compared, the non-blank `customer_id`, `line_display_name`, `email`, `mobile`, `gender`, and `birthday` provided in the imported contact information will be used to overwrite the MAAC contact information
* The above rules do not include `tags`, the system will only tag contacts with new tags, and will not overwrite or remove tags that have been posted by contacts in the past
* Since it takes time to import contact information, you can check the status of the import with `task_id`
* If you want to perform a large number of import behaviors, it is recommended to design the following flow:
    1. Call the API `Import contact`, make the first import, and get the task ID from API Response
    2. Call the API `Check import contact task status` and confirm whether the task of item 1 has been completed or not.
        * Finished → go back to 1. and continue to next import.
        * Not yet completed → wait for 1 second, repeat 2. Confirmation and operation.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `import_key` (required, string) - Specify the field to be aglined with the contact data in the MAAC database
        value: **line_uid**, **customer_id**, **email**, **mobile**
        + data (required, array)
            + (object)
                + `line_uid` (optional, string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
                + `line_display_name` (optional, string) - The name defined by the contact in the official LINE account with maximum 255 characters
                + `email` (optional, string) - Contact email
                + `mobile` (optional, string) - Contact phone number, please use E.164 format. If the number starts with 09XX, it will be automatically converted to E.164 format according to the channel's region.
                + `customer_id` (optional, string) - User ID of the third-party system
                + `gender` (optional, string) - Contact gender
                value: **male**, **female**
                + `tags` (optional, array) - Name array of tags to tag to individual contacts
                    + (string) - tag name
                + `birthday` (optional, string) - Contact's birthday (ISO 8601: YYYY-MM-DD)
        + tags (optional, array) - For all imported contacts, the tag name array of the tags to be attached
            + (string) - Tag name

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "import_key": "line_uid",
                "data": [
                    {
                        "line_uid": "U21d78de43c3ce40fbcbc5c4ce6dfe0b0",
                        "line_display_name": "test_contact1",
                        "email": "alan@example.com",
                        "mobile": "+886987654321",
                        "customer_id": "1235734897",
                        "gender": "male",
                        # personal tags
                        "tags": [
                            "tag1",
                            "tag2"
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "line_uid": "U21d78de43c3ce40fbcbc5c4ce6dfe0b1",
                        "line_display_name": "test_contact1",
                        "email": "alan@example.com",
                        "mobile": "+886987654321",
                        "customer_id": "1235734897",
                        "gender": "male",
                        # personal tags
                        "tags": [
                            "tag1",
                            "tag3"
                        ]
                    }
                ],
                "tags":["20200101import"] # global tags
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - The task id of the imported contact task. It can be used to query the progress of the task.
        + `result` (string) - status description

    + Body

            {
                "id": 999,
                "result": "start importing"
            }

### Check import contact task status [GET /openapi/v1/member/import/{task_id}/]
Check the status of the import contact task by `task_id`. The `response code` represent the status of the checking operation(i.e., the `GET` API call) instead of the task status. In addition, there might be different response bodies when the task statuses are different.

+ Request Import contact is pending (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + task_id : 1 (required, number)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `category` (string) - `import_member`
        + `status` (string) - Contact import status: pending, processing, done
        + `created_at` (string) - creation time
        + `updated_at` (string) - update time

    + Body

            {
                "category": "import_member",
                "status": "pending",
                "created_at": "2021-04-23T22:34:07.360839+08:00",
                "updated_at": "2021-04-23T22:34:07.427273+08:00"
            }

+ Request Import contact is processing (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `category` (string) - `import_member`
        + `status` (string) - Contact import status: pending, processing, done
        + `created_at` (string) - creation time
        + `updated_at` (string) - update time

    + Body

            {
                "category": "import_member",
                "status": "processing",
                "created_at": "2021-04-23T22:34:07.360839+08:00",
                "updated_at": "2021-04-23T22:34:07.427273+08:00"
            }

+ Request Import contact has been successful (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}


+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `category` (string) - `ex:import_member`
        + `status` (string)- Contact import status
        + `result` (object)- detailed report after successful import
            + `tags` (array)
                + (string)-label name
            + `success` (boolean)- whether the import was successful or not
            + `total_num` (number)- the number of the imported users
            + `created_num` (number)- the number of the created users
            + `updated_num` (number)- the number of the updated users
            + `mismatch_num` (number)- The number of the users that do not exist or blocked the LINE OA
            + `mismatch_export_link` (string) - The list of the users that do not exist or blocked the LINE OA(The field is only available when the `import key` is `line_uid`. Otherwise, this field will be `null`.)
            + `start_time` (string)- Import start time
            + `end_time` (string)- Import completion time
        + `created_at` (string)- creation time
        + `updated_at` (string)- update time

    + Body

            {
                "category": "import_member",
                "result": {
                    "tags": [
                        "test tag"
                    ],
                    "success": true,
                    "end_time": "2021-04-23T22:33:06.643646+08:00",
                    "total_num": 2,
                    "start_time": "2021-04-23T22:33:06.031562+08:00",
                    "created_num": 0,
                    "updated_num": 0,
                    "mismatch_num": 2,
                    "mismatch_export_link": "https://storage.googleapis.com/cresclab-maac-production/public/org_368/export_member/XXXXXX.csv"
                },
                "status": "done",
                "created_at": "2021-04-23T22:33:05.936006+08:00",
                "updated_at": "2021-04-23T22:33:06.673536+08:00"
            }

+ Request Import contact has been failed (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}


+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `category` (string) - `ex:import_member`
        + `status` (string)- Contact import status
        + `result` (object)- detailed report after failed import
            + `success` (boolean)- whether the import was successful or not
            + `blank_error` (number) - the number of contacts whose `import_key` field of data are blank
            + `miss_fields` (array) - the missing fields of the contact profile
                + (string) - 欄位名稱
            + `gender_error` (number) - the number of contacts whose gender field is invalid
            + `mobile_error` (number) - the number of contacts whose mobile field is invalid
            + `birthday_error` (number) - the number of contacts whose birthday field is invalid
            + `useless_fields` (array) - the redundant fields of the contact profile
                + (string) - 欄位名稱
            + `duplicate_error` (number) - the number of contacts whose `import_key` field of profiles are duplicated with others'
        + `created_at` (string)- creation time
        + `updated_at` (string)- update time

    + Body

            {
                "category": "import_member",
                "result": {
                    "success": false,
                    "blank_error": 1,
                    "miss_fields": [],
                    "gender_error": 0,
                    "mobile_error": 0,
                    "birthday_error": 0,
                    "useless_fields": [],
                    "duplicate_error": 1
                },
                "status": "done",
                "created_at": "2021-04-23T22:33:05.936006+08:00",
                "updated_at": "2021-04-23T22:33:06.673536+08:00"
            }

## Contact Tracking [/openapi/v1/behavior/download/]
Get the Google Analytics data after the contact clicks the MAAC push message, trace link, rich menu, and the tracking link to the official website, including the following behavioral data.

### Pageview [GET /openapi/v1/behavior/download/{date}/pageview/]

+ Parameters
    + date (required, string, `2017-05-17`) ... date (ISO Format)


+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (text/csv)
    + Headers

            Content-Disposition: attachment; filename={date}_pageview.csv

    + Attributes (object)
        + csv field description (object)
            + `line_uid` (string)- The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
            + `utm_campaign` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_campaign` in MAAC
            + `utm_source` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_source` in MAAC
            + `utm_medium` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_medium` in MAAC
            + `utm_content` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_content` in MAAC
            + `time` (string)- Record time (ISO Format)
            + `page_path` (string)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:pagePath)
            + `page_title` (string)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:pageTitle)
            + `page_views` (number)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:pageviews)
            + `views_per_session` (number)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:pageviewsPerSession)
            + `entrances` (number)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:entrances)
            + `avg_time_on_page` (number)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:avgTimeOnPage)
            + `exits` (number)- [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:exits)
            + `ingestion_timestamp` (string)- time when data was actually ingested into the table

### Product [GET /openapi/v1/behavior/download/{date}/product/]

+ Parameters
    + date (required, string, `2017-05-17`) ... date (ISO Format)


+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (text/csv)
    + Headers

            Content-Disposition: attachment; filename={date}_product.csv

    + Attributes (object)
        + csv field description (object)
            + `line_uid` (string)- The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
            + `utm_campaign` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_campaign` in MAAC
            + `utm_source` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_source` in MAAC
            + `utm_medium` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_medium` in MAAC
            + `utm_content` (string)- Set the tracking code `utm_content` in MAAC
            + `time` (string)- Record time (ISO Format)
            + `product_name` (string) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productName)
            + `product_sku` (string) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productSku)
            + `adds_to_cart` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productAddsToCart)
            + `removes_from_cart` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productRemovesFromCart)
            + `item_revenue` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:itemRevenue)
            + `item_quantity` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:itemQuantity)
            + `checkouts` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productCheckouts)
            + `list_clicks` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productListClicks)
            + `list_views` (number) - [Description](https://ga-dev-tools.appspot.com/dimensions-metrics-explorer/#ga:productListViews)
            + `ingestion_timestamp` (string)- time when data was actually ingested into the table

### Transaction [GET /openapi/v1/behavior/download/{date}/transaction/]

+ Parameters
    + date (required, string, `2017-05-17`) ... date (ISO Format)


