# Group Tag
| column | type | description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
|id| Number | MAAC tag id
| column | String | Tag name
|available_days| Number | The valid number of days after the tag is attached to the contact<br>The `null` value means the tag will be attached permanently.
---

## Tag [/openapi/v1/tag/]

### Get tag list [GET /openapi/v1/tag/{?name,start}]
Get a list of tags of the official account in MAAC. The list is paged for every 300 tags.

* Query Parameter can be used to filter the tags that meet the conditions
* Bring the token in the response `next` parameter of the previous page into the `start` parameter of the request to get the label of the next page

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + name : `fake-tag-name` (optional, string)
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string)-
    The id of the next page will be returned to the `next` parameter of the previous page


+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - Tag array
            + (object)
                + `id` (number) - MAAC tag id
                + `name` (string) - Tag name
                + `available_days` (number) - The valid number of days after the tag is attached to the contact. The `null` value means the tag will be attached permanently.
        + `next` (string) - page token of the next page


    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    {
                        "id": 1,
                        "name": "tag 1",
                        "available_days": null
                    },
                    {...}
                ],
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D"
            }

### Get tag info [GET /openapi/v1/tag/{tag_id}/]

+ Parameters
    + tag_id: `1` (required, number)

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC tag id
        + `name` (string) - Tag name
        + `available_days` (number) - The valid number of days after the tag is attached to the contact. The `null` value means the tag will be attached permanently.

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "fake-tag-name",
                "available_days": 100
            }

### Create tags [POST]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `name` (string) - Tag name
        + `available_days` (number) - The valid number of days after the tag is attached to the contact. Use `null` to attach the tag permanently.


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "name": "fake-tag-name",
                "available_days": 100
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC tag id
        + `name` (string) - Tag name
        + `available_days` (number) - The valid number of days after the tag is attached to the contact. The `null` value means the tag will be attached permanently.

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "fake-tag-name",
                "available_days": 100
            }


## Add or remove tags to contact [/openapi/v1/taglinemember/]
Put new tags on contacts or remove tags that have already been applied.

### Add tags to contact[POST]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `tag_id` (required, number) - MAAC tag ID
        + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "tag_id": 1,
                "line_uid": "U353dc4b8ea88acaa8663c6cd9a4f4000"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `tag_id` (required, number) - MAAC tag ID
        + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
        + `created_at` (string)- Time when the tag was added to the contact (ISO Format)
        + `expired_at` (string)- The expiration time of the tag on the contact (ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "tag_id": 1,
                "line_uid": "U353dc4b8ea88acaa8663c6cd9a4f4000",
                "created_at": "2020-12-17T23:00:00+08",
                "expired_at": "9999-12-31T23:59:59+08"
            }

### Remove tags from contacts [DELETE]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `tag_id` (required, number) - MAAC tag ID
        + `line_uid` (optional, string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "tag_id": 1,
                "line_uid": "U353dc4b8ea88acaa8663c6cd9a4f4000"
            }

+ Response 204


# Group Segment
| column | type | description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| column | Number | segment name
|description| String | segment description
|segment_type| Number | segment type<br>`1`: normal segment<br>`2`: custom segment
|status| Number | Segment status<br>`1`: pending<br>`2`: ready
|member_count| Number | Number of contacts (if `status` not ready yet, member_count will return `-1`)
|last_updated_time| String | Segment last update time(ISO Format)
---

## Segment [/openapi/v1/segment/]

### Get segment list [GET /openapi/v1/segment/{?name,start}]
Get the MAAC segment list, and the list is paged for every 300 segments of the data.

* The default limit for an official account is 30 segments. If you need to purchase more segments, please contact [customer-suport@cresclab.com](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com)
* Bring the token in the response `next` parameter of the previous page into the `start` parameter of the request to get the next segment page.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + name : `fake-tag-name` (optional, string)
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string) -
    The identification code of the next page will be returned to the `next` parameter of the previous page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - segment array
            + (object)
                + `id` (number) - MAAC segment id
                + `name` (string) - MAAC segment name
                + `description` (string) - MAAC segment description
                + `segment_type` (number) - segment type
                value: **normal segment=1**, **custom segment=2**
                + `member_count` (number) - number of contacts
                + `status` (number) - segment status
                value: **pending=1**, **ready=2**
                + `last_updated_time` (string) - segment last update time(ISO Format)
        + `next` (string) - page token of the next page


    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    {
                        "id": 1,
                        "name": "tag_1segment",
                        "description": "contacts tagged with tag_1",
                        "segment_type": 1,
                        "member_count": 100,
                        "status": 2,
                        "last_updated_time": "2020-12-17T23:00:00+08"
                    },
                    {}
                ],
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D"
            }

### Get segment info [GET /openapi/v1/segment/{segment_id}/]

+ Parameters
    + segment_id: `1` (required, number)

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC segment id
        + `name` (string) - MAAC segment name
        + `description` (string) - segment description
        + `segment_type` (number) - segment type
        value: **normal segment=1**, **custom segment=2**
        + `member_count` (number) - number of contacts
        + `status` (number) - segment status
        value: **pending=1**, **ready=2**
        + `last_updated_time` (string) - segment last update time(ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "tag_1segment",
                "description": "contacts tagged with tag_1",
                "segment_type": 1,
                "member_count": 100,
                "status": 2,
                "last_updated_time": "2020-12-17T23:00:00+08"
            }

### Create segments [POST]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `name` (required, string) - segment name
        + `operator` (optional, string) - operational logic unit between the segment filters
        default: *AND*
        + `description` (optional, string) - segment description
        + `tags` (required, array) - tag filter array
            + (object)
                + `status` (required, string) - with or without tags
                value: **with**, *without*
                + `tag_id` (required, number) - MAAC tag id

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "name": "tag_1 & tag_2",
                "operator": "AND",
                "description": "contacts tagged with tag_1 and tag_2",
                "segment_type": 1,
                "tags": [
                    {
                        "status": "with",
                        "tag_id": 1
                    },
                    {
                        "status": "with",
                        "tag_id": 2
                    }
                ]
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC segment id
        + `name` (string) - MAAC segmant name
        + `description` (string) - segmant description
        + `segment_type` (number) - segment type
        value: **normal segment=1**, **custom segment=2**
        + `member_count` (number) - number of contacts
        + `status` (number) - segment status
        value: **pending=1**, **ready=2**
        + `last_updated_time` (string) - segment last update time(ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 2,
                "name": "tag_1 & tag_2",
                "description": "contacts tagged with tag_1 and tag_2",
                "segment_type": 1,
                "member_count": -1,
                "status": 1,
                "last_updated_time": none
            }

### Create segment for uploading custom LINE UIDs [POST /openapi/v1/custom_segment/]
- Create segment by uploading CSV file with LINE UIDs, [file example](https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=12RswSx_9HyBNqs-OEm-O5bZaq1l6aEcb).
- The maximum number of LINE UIDs in one CSV file: 300,000; the maximum size of CSV: 25 MB

+ Request (multipart/form-data)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `name` (required, string) - MAAC segment name
        + `description` (optional, string) - segment description
        + `file` (required, *csv*) - LINE UID CSV file


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "name": "crm remarketing LINE UID list(2021-05-06)",
                "description": "remarketing line uid list from crm",
                "file": *file*
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC segment id
        + `name` (string) - MAAC segment name
        + `description` (string) - segment description
        + `segment_type` (number) - segment type
        value: **normal segment=1**, **custom segment=2**
        + `member_count` (number) - number of contacts
        + `status` (number) - segment status
        value: **pending=1**, **ready=2**
        + `last_updated_time` (string) - segment last upadte time(ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 3,
                "name": "crm remarketing LINE UID list(2021-05-06)",
                "description": "remarketing line uid list from crm",
                "segment_type": 2,
                "member_count": -1,
                "status": 1,
                "last_updated_time": none
            }

### Delete segments [DELETE /openapi/v1/segment/{segment_id}/]

+ Parameters
    + segment_id (required, number, `1`)

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `segment_id` (number) - MAAC segment id

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 204 (application/json)


### Update segment for uploading custom LINE UIDs [PATCH /openapi/v1/custom_segment/{segment_id}/]
- Create segment by uploading CSV file with LINE UIDs, [file example](https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=12RswSx_9HyBNqs-OEm-O5bZaq1l6aEcb).
- The maximum number of LINE UIDs in one CSV file: 300,000; the maximum size of CSV: 25 MB
- `name`、`description`、`file` at least one of above parameters need to be include in Request body.

+ Parameters
    + segment_id (required, number)

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `name` (optional, string) - MAAC segment name
        + `description` (optional, string) - MAAC segment description
        + `file` (optional, *csv*) - LINE UID file

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "name": "crm remarketing LINE UID list(2021-05-07)",
                "description": "remarketing line uid list from crm",
                "file": *file*
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC segment id
        + `name` (string) - MAAC segment name
        + `description` (string) - segment description
        + `segment_type` (number) - segment type
        value: **normal segment=1**, **custom segment=2**
        + `member_count` (number) - number of contacts
        + `status` (number) - segment status
        value: **pending=1**, **ready=2**
        + `last_updated_time` (string) - segment last update time(ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 3,
                "name": "crm remarketing LINE UID list(2021-05-07)",
                "description": "remarketing line uid list from crm",
                "segment_type": 2,
                "member_count": -1,
                "status": 1,
                "last_updated_time": none
            }

### Get the segment contacts LINE UIDs[GET /openapi/v1/segment/{segment_id}/members/]

+ Parameters
    + segment_id: 3 (required, number)

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (text/csv)
    + Headers

            Content-Disposition: attachment; filename={date}_segment_{segment_id}_members.csv

    + Attributes (object)
        + csv column description(object)
            + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length


# Group Message

## Message template [/openapi/v1/template/{?start}]
When sending a message push, you need to fill in the ID of the message template.
The template needs to be created in the "Message Center"> "Message Template Library" of the MAAC.

### Get message template list [GET]

* The list is paginated for every 300 message template data
* Bring the token in the response `next` parameter of the previous page into the `start` parameter of the request to get the message template of the next page

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string) -
    The id of the next page will be returned to the `next` parameter of the previous page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - Array of message template
            + (object)
                + `id` (number) - MAAC message template ID
                + `name` (string) - Message template name
                + `parameters` (array) - The array of parameters in the message template
                    + (string) - Parameter name
        + `next` (string) - the page token of next page


    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    {
                        "id": 1,
                        "name": "best_sellers_recommendation"
                          "parameters": [
                              "store_name",
                              "product_name",
                              "product_price"
                          ]
                    },
                    {}
                ],
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D"
            }

## Message event [/openapi/v1/event/]
When sending a message to push, if you need to track the performance of the message, you need to fill in the event ID. <br><br>

**Notes**<br><br>
MAAC will use the message event to track the performance, and the performance data of the messages pushed with the same message event ID will be integrated.


### Get message event list [GET /openapi/v1/event/{?name,start}]

* The list is paginated for every 300 message template data
* Bring the token in the response `next` parameter of the previous page into the `start` parameter of the request to get the message template of the next page

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + name : `Arrival Notice` (optional, string)
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string) -
    The id of the next page will be returned to the `next` parameter of the previous page

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - Message event array
            + (object)
                + `id` (number)-The ID of the message event in MAAC
                + `archived` (boolean)- This field has been deprecated. Don't use this field.
                + `name` (string)- Message event name
                + `created_at` (string)- Message event created time(ISO Format)
        + `next` (string)- the page token of the next page

    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    {
                        "id": 12,
                        "archived": false,
                        "name": "Arrival Notice",
                        "created_at": "2020-05-27T17:48:56.042752+08:00"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 2,
                        "archived": false,
                        "name": "Marketing Message",
                        "created_at": "2020-05-27T08:00:00+08:00"
                    },
                    {
                        "id": 1,
                        "archived": false,
                        "name": "General Notice",
                        "created_at": "2020-05-27T08:00:00+08:00"
                    }
                ],
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D"
            }

### Get Message event info [GET /openapi/v1/event/{event_id}/]

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + event_id : 1 (required, number)

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number)- MAAC message event ID
        + `archived` (boolean)- This field has been deprecated. Don't use this field.
        + `name` (string)- Message event name
        + `created_at` (string)- message event created time (ISO Format)

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "archived": false,
                "name": "123",
                "created_at": "2020-05-27T08:00:00+08:00"
            }

### Create Message Event [POST]

**🚨 Notice:**  
There is a limit on the number of `event_id`s — the maximum allowed is **1,000**.  
If you encounter the error message: `The number of events has reached the limit`,  
please contact your **Crescendo Lab representative** for assistance.


+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `name` (required, string) - Message event name


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "name": "December marketing news"
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC message event ID
        + `name` (string) - MAAC message event name

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "December marketing news"
            }

## Send message [/openapi/v1/direct_message/]
Three data needed to push the message<br>
* template_id: Create a customized message template through MAAC, and get the message template id<br>
* event_id: Create message event through API and get event id<br>
**🚨Attention: To track performance, be sure to create an event_id to ensure the brand can fully track relevant data!**<br>
* line_uid: the user line_uid to be sent<br>

**Notes**<br>
* When the response status code is `200`, it means that MAAC already sent a message out and already created a sending record for this message, but it does not mean that LINE sent this message to users successfully. For more information about the sending result, please refer to `detail` field in `response` payload.
* The provided value for parameters in a message template should end with an image file extension if this value represents an image. This is because some versions of the computer LINE App cannot show images correctly without an image file extension.
* If the provided value of the parameter represents an image, the image shall follow the below limitations:<br>
  **image format**: JPEG or PNG <br>
  **image aspect ratio**: 1:1 <br>
  **max. image size**: 4096x4096 <br>
  **max. file size**: 1MB <br>
* Messages sent via the Enhanced Multicast API do not support personalized tracking, and there will be no tracking data for opens and clicks.

### Send push message [POST /openapi/v1/direct_message/push/]
Pushing messages to a single user<br><br>

+ **Notes**
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event, if you want to track the performance of the message push, please fill in `event_id`
+ The system will push the message in real time and reply the status in real time
+ There are two possible types of `result` in the message push API response (`string`, `object`), see the example on the right for the different types
+ This API request will be subject to the traffic limits of the LINE Push API. Please refer to [Line rate limit](#line_rate_limits).

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `template_id` (required, number) - message template ID
        + `data` (required, object) - message setting
            + `line_uid` (required, string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
            + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
            + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
        + `event_id` (optional, number) - message event ID, required if you want to track the performance


    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
              "template_id": 45629,
              "event_id": 346,
              "data": {
                  "line_uid":"U1348y18439jefidsgjf924r2",
                  "parameter1": "hello",
                  "parameter2": "world"
              }
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - sending message ID
        + `event_id` (number) - message event ID
        + `result` (string) - sending message status
        value: **success**, **timeout**, **error**

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1342,
                "event": "cart retarget",
                "result": "success"
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - sending message ID
        + `event_id` (number) - message event ID
        + `result` (object) - sending message status
            + `message` (string)- The reason for the error in the LINE reply
            + `details` (array)- the reason for the error
                + `message` (string)- error details
                + `property` (string)- error property

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1342,
                "event": "cart retarget",
                "result": {
                    "message": "The request body has 1 error(s)",
                    "details": [
                        {
                            "message": "Must be one of the following values: [text, image, video, audio, location, sticker, template, imagemap, flex]",
                            "property": "messages[0].type"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }

### Send multicast message [POST /openapi/v1/direct_message/multicast/]
A single push of different messages to a small number of users. A single request can push up to 150 contacts. (Each user's message parameter setting is independent)<br><br>

+ **Notes**
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event, if you want to track the performance of the message push, please fill in `event_id` when requesting
+ The system will use asynchronous push messages, so the current status of the API response is `pending`, if you need to query the push status, you can use [query sending status](#query sending status) to query
+ Up to 150 contacts in a single request
+ This API request will be subject to the traffic limits of the LINE Multicast API. Please refer to [Line rate limit](#line_rate_limits).

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `template_id` (required, number) - message template ID
        + `data` (required, array) - array of push message setting
            + (object)
                + `line_uid` (required, string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
                + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
                + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
        + `event_id` (optional, number) - message event ID, required if you want to track the performance

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "template_id": 45629,
                "event_id": 346,
                "data": [
                    {
                        "line_uid":"U1348y18439jefidsgjf924r2",
                        "parameter1": "hello",
                        "parameter2": "world"
                    },
                    {
                        "line_uid":"Uofkowekgowrpgwrkpglpwlpe",
                        "parameter1": "cresclab",
                        "parameter2": "api"
                    }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - sending message ID
        + `result` (string) - sending message status

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1342,
                "result": "pending"
            }


### Send enhance multicast message [POST /openapi/v1/direct_message/enhanced_multicast/]
A large number of users who push the same message at a time, and a single request pushes up to 500 contacts.

+ **Notes**
+ Each user must use the same set of message parameter settings
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event, if you want to track the performance of the message push, please fill in `event_id` when requesting
+ The system will use asynchronous push messages, so the current status of the API response is `pending`, if you need to query the push status, you can use [query sending status](#query sending status) to query
+ Up to 500 contacts can be pushed in a single request
+ note: The "username" parameter used in the message template does not apply to enhanced multicast, and will not be displayed.
+ note: Personalized information such as prizes is not available in this API, please send via push or multicast API.
+ This API request will be subject to the traffic limits of the LINE Multicast API. Please refer to [Line rate limit](#line_rate_limits).
+ Messages sent via this API do not support personalized tracking, and there will be no tracking data for opens and clicks.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `template_id` (required, number) - message template ID
        + `line_uids` (required, array) - the array of the unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account
            + (required, string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
        + `data` (required, object) - message setting
            + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
            + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the message template: name vs. value
        + `event_id` (optional, number) - message event ID, required if you want to track the performance

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "template_id": 45629,
                "line_uids": [
                    "U1348y18439jefidsgjf924r2....",
                    "Uofkowekgowrpgwrkpglpwlpe...."
                ],
                "data": {
                    "parameter1": "hello",
                    "parameter2": "world"
                },
                "event_id": 346
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - sending message ID
        + `result` (string) - sending message status

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1342,
                "result": "pending"
            }

## Sending message status [/openapi/v1/direct_message/{direct_message_id}/]
<a name="query sending message status"></a>

### Query sending message status [GET]
Used to query the sending status of past push messages, including: send message, send multicast message, and send enhanced message.
The value of the `status` field will be one of the following: `pending`, `sending`, and `sent`. The `result` field will be returned once the message is in `sent` status.

+ **Notes**
+ if the response status code is 200, it means MAAC has this sending record.
+ if `fail_info` value exists, it is highly possible that LINE failed to send this message out. Please assess whether to resend this or not.

+ Parameters
    + direct_message_id: `1` (required, number)

+ Request (application/json)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC event id
        + `category` (string) - message type: push, multicast
        + `status` (string) - sending status
        + `result` (object) - result ( **multicast** )
            + `sent_time` (string) -
            + `to` (object) -
                + `line_ids` (array)
                    + `line_id` (string)
            + `total_count` (number) - total number of messages sent
            + `fail_count` (number) - number of failed message sending
            + `fail_info` (array) - failure details for each failed message
                + (object)
                    + `line_uid` (string) - LINE user ID that failed
                    + `mark` (number) - position index in original push/multicast LINE IDs array (0-indexed)
                    + `response` (string) - error message from LINE or internal error

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "category": "multicast",
                "status": "sent",
                "event_id": null,
                "result": {
                    "sent_time": "2024-01-15T10:30:00+08:00",
                    "to": {
                    "line_ids": [
                        "U11111111111111111111111111111111",
                        "U22222222222222222222222222222222",
                        "U33333333333333333333333333333333"
                    ]
                    },
                    "total_count": 5,
                    "fail_count": 3,
                    "fail_info": [
                        {
                            "line_uid": "U11111111111111111111111111111111",
                            "mark": 0,
                            "response": "timeout"
                        },
                        {
                            "line_uid": "U22222222222222222222222222222222",
                            "mark": 2,
                            "response": "{\"message\": \"Invalid user\"}"
                        },
                        {
                            "line_uid": "U33333333333333333333333333333333",
                            "mark": 3,
                            "response": "429 Too Many Requests"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }

## Message performance [/openapi/v1/event/{event_id}/report/{?start_date,end_date}]

### Get message performance report [GET /openapi/v1/event/{event_id}/report/{?start_date,end_date}]
Used to query the performance report in the past push messages. <br><br>

+ **Notes**
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event. If you want to get the message performance, please fill in the event_id when pushing.
+ When requesting, you can set the start and end dates for the calculation of the performance report
+ The field `unique_clicks` will be available from 2022-10-05. Note that it is nullable if there is no data source.
+ Messages sent via the Enhanced Multicast API do not support personalized tracking, so there will be no data on opens and clicks.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + event_id : 1 (required, number)
    + start_date : `2017-05-17` (optional, string) ... start date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**
    + end_date : `2020-05-17` (optional, string) ... end date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - MAAC message event ID
        + `report` (object)
            + `total` (object)
                + `clicks` (number) - total clicks
                + `unique_clicks` (number, nullable) - unique clicks
                + `adds_to_cart` (number) - add to cart count
                + `transactions` (number) - transaction count
                + `transaction_revenue` (number) - transaction revenue
                + `opens` (number) - open count
            + `urls` (array) - URL tracking data
                + (object)
                    + `id` (number) - URL tracking ID
                    + `link` (number) - link ID
                    + `url` (string) - the tracked URL
                    + `utm_campaign` (string, nullable) - UTM campaign parameter
                    + `utm_source` (string, nullable) - UTM source parameter
                    + `utm_medium` (string, nullable) - UTM medium parameter
                    + `utm_content` (string, nullable) - UTM content parameter
                    + `clicks` (number) - total clicks
                    + `unique_clicks` (number, nullable) - unique clicks
                    + `adds_to_cart` (number) - add to cart count
                    + `transactions` (number) - transaction count
                    + `transaction_revenue` (number) - transaction revenue
                    + `tags` (array) - associated tags
            + `messages` (array) - trigger keyword tracking data
                + (object)
                    + `id` (number) - message tracking ID
                    + `message` (string) - trigger keyword in message template
                    + `clicks` (number) - click count
                    + `tags` (array) - associated tags


    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "report": {
                    "total": {
                        "opens": 1234,
                        "clicks": 567,
                        "unique_clicks": 432,
                        "adds_to_cart": 89,
                        "transactions": 23,
                        "transaction_revenue": 12500.00
                    },
                    "urls": [
                        {
                            "id": 1,
                            "link": 101,
                            "url": "https://example.com/product",
                            "utm_campaign": "summer_sale",
                            "utm_source": "line",
                            "utm_medium": "message",
                            "utm_content": "banner",
                            "clicks": 150,
                            "unique_clicks": 120,
                            "adds_to_cart": 30,
                            "transactions": 8,
                            "transaction_revenue": 4500.00,
                            "tags": ["promo", "summer"]
                        }
                    ],
                    "messages": [
                        {
                            "id": 1,
                            "message": "Buy now",
                            "clicks": 75,
                            "tags": ["cta", "purchase"]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            }


# Group Deeplink

## Deeplink [/openapi/v1/deeplink/]

### Get deeplink performance report [GET /openapi/v1/deeplink/{?start_date,end_date}]
Get the performance report of the deeplink.<br><br>

+ **Notes**
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event. If you want to get the message performance, please fill in the event_id when pushing.
+ When requesting, you can set the start and end dates for the calculation of the performance report

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + start_date : `2017-05-17` (optional, string) ... start date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**
    + end_date : `2020-05-17` (optional, string) ... end date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - deeplink ID
        + `name` (string) - deeplink name
        + `description` (string) - deeplink description
        + `shorten_url` (string) - deeplink shorten_url
        + `created_at` (string) - deeplink created time(ISO Format)
        + `tags` (array) - tag name array of the tags to be attached
                + (string)
        + `report` (object) - performance report
            + `click_count` (number) - click count
            + `auth_count` (number) - auth contact count
            + `new_friend_count` (number) - new contact count
            + `existing_friend_count` (number) - existing contact count
            + `unique_auth_count` (number) - unique auth count
            + `unique_new_friend_count` (number) - unique new contact count
            + `unique_existing_friend_count` (number) - unique existing contact count



    + Body

            {
                "id": 1,
                "name": "deeplink_1",
                "description": "1st deeplink",
                "shorten_url": "https://maac.io/xxxxx",
                "created_at": "2020-07-27T14:52:41.874151+08:00",
                "tags": ["tag_1", "tag_2"],
                "report": {
                    "click_count": 0,
                    "auth_count": 0,
                    "new_friend_count": 0,
                    "existing_friend_count": 0,
                    "unique_auth_count": 0,
                    "unique_new_friend_count": 0,
                    "unique_existing_friend_count": 0
                }
            }

# Group Tracelink

## Tracelink [/openapi/v1/tracelink/]

### Get tracelink performance report [GET /openapi/v1/tracelink/{?start_date,end_date}]
Get the performance report of the tracelink.<br><br>

+ **Notes**
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event. If you want to get the message performance, please fill in the event_id when pushing.
+ When requesting, you can set the start and end dates for the calculation of the performance report
+ The field `unique_clicks` will be available from 2022-09-16. Note that it is nullable if there is no data source.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + start_date : `2017-05-17` (optional, string) ... start date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**
    + end_date : `2020-05-17` (optional, string) ... end date **(YYYY-MM-DD)**

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - Identifier for the TraceLink in MAAC.
        + `name` (string) - The name of the TraceLink.
        + `description` (string, nullable) - Description of the TraceLink. Can be null.
        + `shorten_url` (string) - The shortened URL for the TraceLink.
        + `created_at` (string) - Timestamp when the TraceLink was created (ISO 8601 Format).
        + `tag` (array[string]) - List of tags associated with the TraceLink (can be an empty array).
        + `report` (object) - Summary performance report data for this TraceLink.
            + `clicks` (number) - Total number of clicks.
            + `unique_clicks` (number, nullable) - Number of unique clicks. Null if data is unavailable. (Note: Feature enabled 2022-09-16)
            + `adds_to_cart` (number) - Number of times items were added to the cart.
            + `transactions` (number) - Total number of transactions.
            + `transaction_revenue` (number) - Total revenue generated from transactions.
        + `utm` (object, nullable) - UTM parameters associated with this TraceLink. May be null or an empty object if not configured.
            + `utm_campaign` (string) - UTM campaign name (utm_campaign).
            + `utm_source` (string) - UTM source (utm_source).
            + `utm_medium` (string) - UTM medium (utm_medium).
            + `utm_content` (string) - UTM content (utm_content).

    + Body

            {
                "id": 388101,
                "name": "This is for TraceLink",
                "description": null,
                "shorten_url": "https://maac.io/3iuM7",
                "created_at": "2025-01-23T17:41:37.142001+08:00",
                "tag": [],
                "report": {
                    "clicks": 5,
                    "unique_clicks": null,
                    "adds_to_cart": 0,
                    "transactions": 0,
                    "transaction_revenue": 0
                },
                "utm": {
                    "utm_campaign": "20241111",
                    "utm_source": "LINE",
                    "utm_medium": "offline",
                    "utm_content": "taipei_branch"
                }
            }

# Group Bindlink

## Bindlink [/openapi/v1/binding/bindlink/]

### Generate bindlink [POST]
From the left column of MAAC > Message Center > Message Template Library > Binding Message Template, after creating a message template, you can get the created template ID.

+ **Notes**
+  If you want to update a bound contact data, please use [Update member](#reference/0/0/3)API。

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `bind_link_id` (required, number) - message template ID
        + `customer_id` (required, string) - User ID of the third-party system
        + `email` (optional, string) - contact email
        + `mobile` (optional, string) - contact phone number
        + `bind_once` (optional, boolean) - If true, the generated bindlink can only be bound once. If false or omitted, bindlink can be bound multiple times (default behavior)

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
              "customer_id": "1235734897",
              "bind_link_id": 1,
              "bind_once": false    
            }

+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `link` (string) - bindlink
        + `is_login` (boolean)- whether this `customer_id` has been tied to the contact of the official account
        + `line_display_name` (optional, string)- If the above is `True`, then reply to the user name bound to the `customer_id`

    + Body

            {
                "link": "https://maac.io/XXXX",
                "is_login": false
            }


## Callback [/partner/maac/binding/callback/]

### Callback [POST]
When the user clicks the binding link and joins the official account to complete the binding, MAAC will send event notifications through the registered callback endpoint. (To log in to the callback endpoint, please contact [Customer support](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com))

(MAAC OpenAPI does not have the endpoint `/partner/maac/binding/callback/`, please do not use this for testing, this is just a design example, for reference only)

>#### **Request**

`POST https://your-api-domain.com/your/callback/endpoint`

>#### **Headers**

| column | value |
| :-- | :-- |
|`<custom-preset-header-key>`| `<custom-preset-header-value>` |

>#### **Body**

| column | type | description |
| -- | -- | -- |
|line_uid | String | The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
|customer_id| String | User ID of the third-party system
|email| String | Contact email
|mobile| String | Contact phone Number
|status| String | Contact status <br>`follow`: contacts of the official account<br>`auth`: the contact has authorized the official account<br>`unfollow`: the contact has blocked the official account

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `line_uid` (string) - The unique user ID of the contact in the LINE official account, 33 characters in length
        + `customer_id` (string) - User ID of the third-party system
        + `email` (string) - Contact email
        + `mobile` (string) - Contact phone Number
        + `status` (string) - Contact status


    + Headers

            x-api-key: api_key_here

    + Body

            {
                "line_uid": "U12345678901234567890123456789012",
                "customer_id": "C123456789",
                "email": "sample@cresclab.com",
                "mobile": "0912345678",
                "status": "follow",
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Body

            {}

# Group Prize

## Prize [/openapi/v1/prize/]

### Redeem Prize [POST /openapi/v1/prize/{code}/redeem/]
Redeem the prize with unique code.<br><br>

**Notes**
+ This is the request for Voucher redemption only.
+ Please try not to press the redeem button and send the request by POS machine at the same time.

#### **Parameters**

| column | type | option |description |
| -- | -- | -- | -- |
| code | String(32) | required | The unique prize code of Voucher.

#### **Body**

| column | type | option | description |
| -- | -- | -- | -- |
| tags | Array[String(255)] | optional | A List of MAAC tag names for contact.<br> Max number of tags: 5.<br>Max length of name: 255.
|customer_id| String(1024) | required, nullable | User ID of the third-party system
|mobile| String(16) | required, nullable | Contact phone number
|gender| String | required, nullable | Contact gender.<br> value:<br> - `male`<br>- `female`<br>- `unknown`
|store| String(16) | required, nullable | Vender name
|revenue| Float | required, nullable | Revenue per redemption

#### **Response**

###### response body

 ```json
 {
    "detail": <success/error message>
 }
 ```

| status code | detail | description |
| -- | -- | -- |
| 201 | Success | The prize redemption is successful.
| 403 | Token Invalid | The API token is lacking or invalid.
| 404 | Prize Code Does Not Exist | Prize not found.
| 404 | Prize Status Expired | The Prize validity is expired.
| 404 | Contact Not Found | Contact not found.
| 408 | Prize Redemption Need Retry | Transaction blocking (e.g., while the other is changing prize setting/data), needs to retry.
| 409 | Prize Has Been Redeemed | The current prize has been redeemed.
| 409 | Prize Is Not Received | The current prize is not "received".
| 500 | Other errors | Unknown error.

+ Parameters
    + code: `xxx12345` (optional, string) - Prize code max length: 32<br>

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `tags` (optional, array[string]) - A list of tags name.
            default: `[]`.
            Max number: 5.
            Max length of tag name: 255.
        + `customer_id` (required, string, nullable) - User ID of the third-party system (can be `null`)
            Max length: 1024.
        + `mobile` (required, string, nullable) - Contact phone number (can be `null`)
            Max length: 16.
        + `gender` (required, string, nullable) - Contact gender (can be `null`)
            value: **male**, **female**, **unknown**
        + `store`  (required, string, nullable) - Vendor name (can be `null`)
            Max length: 1024.
        + `revenue` (required, number, nullable) - Revenue per redemption (can be `null`)
           default: `0.0` if `null`.

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
              "tags": ["1111 Activity", "1111 Acitivity 2"]
              "customer_id": "1235734897",
              "mobile": "0912345678",
              "gender": "unknown",
              "store": "CrescLab",
              "revenue": 1.0,
            }


+ Response 201 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `detail` (string) - success/error message
    + Body

            {
                "detail": "Success"
            }

+ Response 403 (application/json)
    + Body

            {
                "detail": "Token Invalid"
            }


# Group Auto Reply

## Auto Reply Report [/openapi/v1/auto_reply/]

### Search Auto Reply Reports [POST /openapi/v1/auto_reply/search/]

Search and retrieve auto reply report data with support for filtering by time range and channel type.

**Notes**

- It is recommended to keep the date range within 3 months for optimal performance
- Terminology Notes:
  - `new_friend`: New Contact
  - `original_friend`: Unbound Contact
  - `bound_friend`: Bound Contact

#### **Request Body**

| Field | Type | Required | Default | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- | :-- | :-- |
| start_date | String | optional | `"2016-01-01"` | Start date (YYYY-MM-DD)
| end_date | String | optional | Today | End date (YYYY-MM-DD)
| channel_type | String | optional | `null` | Channel type filter
| offset | Integer | optional | `0` | Pagination offset
| limit | Integer | optional | `20` | Items per page (1-20)

**Field Details**

- **start_date / end_date**
  - Format: `YYYY-MM-DD` (e.g., `2025-01-15`)
  - Validation: `start_date` must be ≤ `end_date`
  - Purpose: Define the time range for report statistics

- **channel_type**
  - Available values:
    - `line` - LINE Official Account
    - `whatsapp` - WhatsApp Business
    - `wccs` - web chat
    - `fb` - Facebook Messenger
    - `ig` - Instagram Messaging
  - Purpose: Return only auto reply data for the specified channel type

- **offset / limit**
  - offset: Number of records to skip (≥ 0)
  - limit: Number of records to return (1-20)
  - Purpose: Implement pagination

#### **Response (200 OK)**

**Root Level Fields**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| count | Integer | Total number of auto replies matching the criteria (for pagination)
| reports | Array | Report statistics data

**Report Object**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| id | Integer | Auto reply ID
| name | String | Auto reply name
| created_at | String | Auto reply creation time (ISO 8601)
| start_date | String | Report start date (YYYY-MM-DD)
| end_date | String | Report end date (YYYY-MM-DD)
| total | Object | Overall statistics
| channel_setting_reports | Array | Detailed statistics by channel

**TotalReport Object (total)**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| triggers | Integer | Number of triggers
| replies | Integer | Number of replies
| opens | Integer | Number of opens
| unique_opens | Integer | Number of unique opens
| clicks | Integer | Number of clicks
| unique_clicks | Integer | Number of unique clicks
| click_rate | Float | Click rate (clicks / triggers)
| adds_to_cart | Integer | Number of add-to-cart actions
| orders | Integer | Number of orders
| revenue | Float | Revenue amount

**ChannelSettingReport Object**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| id | Integer | Channel setting ID
| channel_id | Integer | Channel (Bot) ID
| channel_type | String | Channel type
| channel_name | String | Channel name
| total | Object | Overall statistics for this channel (same structure as TotalReport)
| new_friend | Object | Statistics for new contacts
| original_friend | Object | Statistics for unbound contacts
| bound_friend | Object | Statistics for bound contacts

**MessageReport Object (new_friend / original_friend / bound_friend)**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| total | Object | Statistics for this contact type (same structure as TotalReport)
| urls | Array | URL click and conversion statistics
| messages | Array | Interactive message click statistics

**UrlMetric Object (urls array element)**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| id | Integer | Link ID
| utm_campaign | String | UTM tracking parameter - campaign name
| utm_source | String | UTM tracking parameter - source (e.g., LINE, WhatsApp)
| utm_medium | String | UTM tracking parameter - medium (e.g., message)
| utm_content | String | UTM tracking parameter - content description
| clicks | Integer | Number of clicks
| adds_to_cart | Integer | Number of add-to-cart actions
| transactions | Integer | Number of transactions (orders)
| transaction_revenue | Float | Transaction amount (revenue)
| link | Integer | Link ID (same as id)
| tags | Array[String] | Tag list (for classification)

**MessageMetric Object (messages array element)**

| Field | Type | Description |
| :-- | :------- | :-- |
| id | Integer | Message/button ID
| message | String | Message/button text content
| tags | Array[String] | Related tag list
| clicks | Integer | Number of clicks

**Notes**
- **`urls` purpose**: Track the performance of external links in messages (e.g., product pages, official website) with complete UTM parameters and conversion data
- **`messages` purpose**: Track clicks on interactive message elements (e.g., LINE Quick Reply, Postback Action)
- **Conversion tracking**: The `adds_to_cart`, `transactions`, and `transaction_revenue` in `urls` require GA integration to obtain data

+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `start_date` (optional, string) - Start date (YYYY-MM-DD)
            Default: `"2016-01-01"`.
        + `end_date` (optional, string) - End date (YYYY-MM-DD)
            Default: Today.
        + `channel_type` (optional, string) - Channel type filter
            Available values: `line`, `whatsapp`, `wccs`, `fb`, `ig`.
        + `offset` (optional, number) - Pagination offset
            Default: `0`.
            Must be >= 0.
        + `limit` (optional, number) - Items per page
            Default: `20`.
            Range: 1-20.

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
              "start_date": "2025-01-01",
              "end_date": "2025-01-07",
              "channel_type": "line",
              "offset": 0,
              "limit": 10
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `count` (number) - Total number of auto replies matching the criteria
        + `reports` (array) - Report statistics data
            + (object)
                + `id` (number) - Auto reply ID
                + `name` (string) - Auto reply name
                + `created_at` (string) - Auto reply creation time (ISO 8601)
                + `start_date` (string) - Report start date (YYYY-MM-DD)
                + `end_date` (string) - Report end date (YYYY-MM-DD)
                + `total` (object) - Overall statistics
                    + `triggers` (number) - Number of triggers
                    + `replies` (number) - Number of replies
                    + `opens` (number) - Number of opens
                    + `unique_opens` (number) - Number of unique opens
                    + `clicks` (number) - Number of clicks
                    + `unique_clicks` (number) - Number of unique clicks
                    + `click_rate` (number) - Click rate
                    + `adds_to_cart` (number) - Number of add-to-cart actions
                    + `orders` (number) - Number of orders
                    + `revenue` (number) - Revenue amount
                + `channel_setting_reports` (array) - Detailed statistics by channel
                    + (object)
                        + `id` (number) - Channel setting ID
                        + `channel_id` (number) - Channel (Bot) ID
                        + `channel_type` (string) - Channel type
                        + `channel_name` (string) - Channel name
                        + `total` (object) - Overall statistics for this channel
                            + `triggers` (number) - Number of triggers
                            + `replies` (number) - Number of replies
                            + `opens` (number) - Number of opens
                            + `unique_opens` (number) - Number of unique opens
                            + `clicks` (number) - Number of clicks
                            + `unique_clicks` (number) - Number of unique clicks
                            + `click_rate` (number) - Click rate
                            + `adds_to_cart` (number) - Number of add-to-cart actions
                            + `orders` (number) - Number of orders
                            + `revenue` (number) - Revenue amount
                        + `new_friend` (object) - Statistics for new contacts
                            + `total` (object) - Statistics (same structure as above)
                                + `triggers` (number) - Number of triggers
                                + `replies` (number) - Number of replies
                                + `opens` (number) - Number of opens
                                + `unique_opens` (number) - Number of unique opens
                                + `clicks` (number) - Number of clicks
                                + `unique_clicks` (number) - Number of unique clicks
                                + `click_rate` (number) - Click rate
                                + `adds_to_cart` (number) - Number of add-to-cart actions
                                + `orders` (number) - Number of orders
                                + `revenue` (number) - Revenue amount
                            + `urls` (array) - URL click and conversion statistics
                                + (object)
                                    + `id` (number) - Link ID
                                    + `utm_campaign` (string) - UTM campaign name
                                    + `utm_source` (string) - UTM source
                                    + `utm_medium` (string) - UTM medium
                                    + `utm_content` (string) - UTM content description
                                    + `clicks` (number) - Number of clicks
                                    + `adds_to_cart` (number) - Number of add-to-cart actions
                                    + `transactions` (number) - Number of transactions
                                    + `transaction_revenue` (number) - Transaction amount
                                    + `link` (number) - Link ID
                                    + `tags` (array[string]) - Tag list
                            + `messages` (array) - Interactive message click statistics
                                + (object)
                                    + `id` (number) - Message/button ID
                                    + `message` (string) - Message/button text content
                                    + `tags` (array[string]) - Related tag list
                                    + `clicks` (number) - Number of clicks
                        + `original_friend` (object) - Statistics for unbound contacts
                            + `total` (object) - Statistics (same structure as new_friend.total)
                            + `urls` (array) - URL click and conversion statistics (same structure as new_friend.urls)
                            + `messages` (array) - Interactive message click statistics (same structure as new_friend.messages)
                        + `bound_friend` (object) - Statistics for bound contacts
                            + `total` (object) - Statistics (same structure as new_friend.total)
                            + `urls` (array) - URL click and conversion statistics (same structure as new_friend.urls)
                            + `messages` (array) - Interactive message click statistics (same structure as new_friend.messages)

    + Body

            {
              "count": 2,
              "reports": [
                {
                  "id": 1,
                  "name": "Welcome Message",
                  "created_at": "2025-01-01T10:00:00+08:00",
                  "start_date": "2025-01-01",
                  "end_date": "2025-01-07",
