# Group SMS+

This section describes how to use SMS+ related APIs.

## SMS+ campaign [/openapi/v1/pnp/setting/]

When sending a SMS+ message, you need to fill in a SMS+ campagin ID.
If the campaign enables Line Notification Message, the template needs to be reviewed by the LINE official first; Crescendo Lab will assist in completing the application.

Please contact [Customer support](mailto:customer-supoort@cresclab.com) for the
application.

### Get SMS+ campaign [GET /openapi/v1/pnp/setting/{?start}]

Get the list of SMS+ campaigns. The list is paginated for every
`300` campaigns.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string) -
      The cursor of the next page. It will be returned in the `next` parameter of the previous page.

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - The array of SMS+ campaigns
            + (object)
                + `id` (number) - SMS+ campaign ID
                + `name` (string) - SMS+ campaign name
                + `status` (string) - SMS+ campaign status
                + `line_push_enabled` (boolean) - Enable LINE PUSH Message or not
                + `pnp_enabled` (boolean) - Enable LINE Notification Message or not
                + `fallback_enabled` (boolean) - Enable SMS Message or not
                + `fallback_period` (number) - Forwarding SMS waiting time (minutes)
                + `parameters` (array) - Parameter array in LINE Notification Message
                    + (string) - parameter name
                + `sms_parameters` (array) - Parameter array in SMS message
                    + (string) - parameter name
        + `next` (string) - the page token of the next page. `null` if no next page.


    + Body

            {
                "results": [
                    "id": 1111,
                    "name": "Arrival Notice",
                    "status": "enable",
                    "line_push_enabled": true,
                    "pnp_enabled": true,
                    "fallback_enabled": true,
                    "fallback_period": 1440,
                    "parameters": [
                        "days",
                        "location_name",
                        "order_number",
                        "arrival_date",
                        "order_url"
                    ],
                    "sms_parameters": [
                        "order_number",
                        "arrival_date",
                        "location_name",
                        "days"
                    ]
                ],
                "next": null
            }

### Get SMS+ campaign info [GET /openapi/v1/pnp/setting/{pnp_setting_id}/]

Get the specified SMS+ campaign and its statistics metrics.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + `pnp_setting_id` : 1111 (required, number) - SMS+ campaign ID

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - SMS+ campaign ID
        + `name` (string) - SMS+ campaign name
        + `status` (string) - SMS+ campaign stauts
        + `line_push_enabled` (boolean) - Enable LINE PUSH Message or not
        + `pnp_enabled` (boolean) - Enable LINE Notification Message or not
        + `fallback_enabled` (boolean) - Enable SMS Message or not
        + `fallback_period` (number) - Forwarding SMS waiting time (minutes)
        + `parameters` (array) - Parameter array in LINE Notification Message
            + (string) - parameter name
        + `sms_parameters` (array) - Parameter array in SMS message
            + (string) - parameter name
        + `metric` (object) - SMS+ message statistics
            + `all` (number) - Total number of SMS+ message triggered
            + `fail` (number) - Total number of SMS+ message fail
            + `pnp` (number) - Total number of LINE Notification Messages
            + `sms` (number) - Total number of SMS Messages

    + Body

            {
                "id": 1111,
                "name": "Arrival Notice",
                "status": "enable",
                "line_push_enabled": true,
                "pnp_enabled": true,
                "fallback_enabled": true,
                "fallback_period": 1440,
                "parameters": [
                    "days",
                    "location_name",
                    "order_number",
                    "arrival_date",
                    "order_url"
                ],
                "sms_parameters": [
                    "order_number",
                    "arrival_date",
                    "location_name",
                    "days"
                ],
                "metric": {
                    "all": 0,
                    "fail": 0,
                    "pnp": 0,
                    "sms": 0
                }
            }


## Send SMS+ message [/openapi/v1/pnp/message/]

Required information for sending SMS+ messages

- `pnp_setting_id`: SMS+ campaign ID, which needs to be approved by LINE.
- `phone_number`: The mobile phone number of the user.

The phone number format supports the following formats:
- **E.164** format: An international telephone numbering plan (e.g., `+886912345678`).
- **SHA256-hashed** format: A SHA256-hashed E.164 phone number (64 lowercase hexadecimal characters, e.g., `e3b0c44298fc1c149afbf4c8996fb92427ae41e4649b934ca495991b7852b855`). **Note: SHA256-hashed phone numbers are only accepted if SMS is disabled in the given SMS+ template (PNP setting). Also, LINE Push only supports exact match, so E.164 and SHA256 are incompatible for LINE Push.**

The content of LINE Notification Message must be approved by LINE before it can be used.

### Send single LINE SMS+ message [POST /openapi/v1/pnp/message/push/]

Send SMS+ message to a single user.

+ **Notes**
+ Once you get `200` status code from the API, it means we already kept your LINE
Notification Message request in our system. You don't need to retry in this case.
+ We would automatically fallback to SMS if SMS+ message cannot be
delivered successfully in the `fallback_period`.
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event, if you want to track the performance of the message push, please fill in `event_id`


+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `pnp_setting_id` (required, number) - SMS+ campaign ID
        + `event_id` (optional, number) - message event ID, required if you want to track the performance
        + `data` (required, object) - setting
            + `phone_number` (required, string) - The contact's phone number. Accepts E.164 format (e.g., `+886912345678`) or SHA256-hashed E.164 format (64 hex chars). SHA256 is only accepted when SMS is disabled in the SMS+ template. LINE Push only supports exact match (E.164 and SHA256 incompatible).
            + `line_push_template_id` (optional, number) - The ID of MESSAGE TEMPLATE. Required for SMS+ campaigns which enables LINE Push Message.
            + `line_push` (optional, object) - LINE Push Message setting. Required for SMS+ campaigns which enables LINE Push Message.
                + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Push Message template: name vs. value
                + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Push Message template: name vs. value
            + `pnp` (required, object) - LINE Notification Message setting
                + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Notification Message template: name vs. value
                + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Notification Message template: name vs. value
            + `sms` (required, object) - SMS setting
                + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the SMS template: name vs. value
                + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the SMS template: name vs. value
            + `whatsapp` (optional, object) - WhatsApp Template Message setting
                + `template_name` (required, string) - WhatsApp template name
                + `language` (required, string) - WhatsApp template language
                + `template_data` (required, object) - WhatsApp template variables
                    + `header` (optional, object) - whatsapp template header
                        + `parameters` (array) - whatsapp template header parameters
                            + (string) - parameter content
                            + (object) - parameter content
                                + `type` (enum) - parameter type
                                    + text - text type
                                    + image - image type
                                    + video - video type
                                    + document - document type
                                    + location - location type
                                + `text` (optional, string) - text content. Required if type is text.
                                + `media_id` (optional, string) - WhatsApp Media Object ID. Required if type is image, video or document and media_url is not used.
                                + `media_url` (optional, string) - Media URL. Required if type is image, video or document and media_id is not used.
                                + `filename` (optional, string) - filename. Required if type is document.
                                + `latitude` (optional, string) - latitude value. Required if type is location.
                                + `longitude` (optional, string) - longitude value. Required if type is location.
                                + `name` (optional, string) - name. Required if type is location.
                                + `address` (optional, string) - address. Required if type is location.
                    + `body` (optional, object) - WhatsApp template body
                        + `parameters` (array[string]) - whatsapp template body parameters
            + `customized_id` (optional, string) - A user-defined ID for tracking or correlating messages across systems.
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "pnp_setting_id": 1111,
                "event_id": 123,
                "data": {
                    "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                    "line_push_template_id": 123,
                    "line_push": {
                        "days": "7",
                        "location_name": "A store",
                        "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                        "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                        "order_url": "http://your.domain.com/order/"
                    },
                    "pnp": {
                        "days": "7",
                        "location_name": "A store",
                        "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                        "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                        "order_url": "http://your.domain.com/order/"
                    },
                    "sms": {
                        "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                        "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                        "location_name": "A store",
                        "days": "7"
                    },
                    "whatsapp": {
                        "template_name": "deliver_confirmation_test",
                        "template_data": {
                            "header": {
                                "parameters": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "text",
                                        "text": "A store"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            "body": {
                                "parameters": ["AJ1234567"]
                            }
                        },
                        "language": "en_US"
                     },
                     "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                }
            }

+ Request Use WhatsApp image header template message (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "pnp_setting_id": 1111,
                "event_id": 123,
                "data": {
                    "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                    "pnp": {},
                    "sms": {
                        "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                        "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                        "location_name": "A store",
                        "days": "7"
                    },
                    "whatsapp": {
                        "template_name": "deliver_confirmation_test",
                        "template_data": {
                            "header": {
                                "parameters": [
                                    {
                                        "type": "image",
                                        "media_url": "http://maac.io/xxxxx.jpg"
                                    }
                                ]
                            },
                            "body": {
                                "parameters": ["AJ1234567"]
                            }
                        },
                        "language": "en_US"
                     },
                     "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                }
            }


+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `id` (number) - SMS+ message ID.  Matches the `pnp_message_id` in the webhook and the `pnp_message_id` field in the "Get Sending Records List" API.
        + `result` (string)
          SMS+ message status
            + `success` - This message has been submitted to LINE.
            + `we're under maintenance` - LINE is under maintaince; this message will be delivered via SMS after `fallback_period`.
            + `failed to send messages` - LINE cannot match the phone number; this message will be delivered via SMS after `fallback_period`.
            + `access token expired` - LINE token is not valid; this message will be delivered via SMS after `fallback_period`.
            + `timeout` - LINE API timeout; this message will be delivered via SMS after `fallback_period`.
            + There might be other unlisted status. The system would deliver the message via SMS after `fallback_period`.
    + Body

            {
                "id": 1342,
                "result": "success"
            }

+ Response 400 (text/plain)
    - `pnp setting not found` - SMS+ campaign ID is invalid
    - `xxx field is required` - Missing required field in the used SMS+ campaign
    - `this value does not match the required pattern` - The phone number format is invalid
    - `your SMS points are insufficient, please recharge before sending` - You don't have enough MAAC point quato; please contact us

    + Body

            pnp setting not found

+ Response 403 (text/plain)
    - `You do not have permission to perform this action` - The authorization token is invalid

    + Body

            You do not have permission to perform this action

+ Response 503 (text/plain)
    - `failed to emit messages` - The request meets a temporarily service unavailable. Please try again later.

    + Body

            failed to emit messages

### Send multicast SMS+ messages [POST /openapi/v1/pnp/message/multicast/]

Send multicast SMS+ messages to multiple users (up to **150** users). The parameter
settings of each user could be different.
**Noted, the API does not support LINE Push Message.**

+ **Notes**
+ Once you get `200` status code from the API, it means we already kept your LINE
Notification Message request in our system. You don't need to retry in this case.
+ The system will process the messages asynchronously, so the status of the API response is `pending`.
+ We would automatically fallback to SMS if SMS+ message cannot be
delivered successfully in the `fallback_period`.
+ MAAC will track the performance of the message event, if you want to track the performance of the message push, please fill in `event_id`


+ Request (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `pnp_setting_id` (required, number) - SMS+ campaign ID
        + `event_id` (optional, number) - message event ID, required if you want to track the performance
        + `data` (required, array) - the array of SMS+ campaign setting
            + (object)
                + `phone_number` (required, string) - The contact's phone number. Accepts E.164 format (e.g., `+886912345678`) or SHA256-hashed E.164 format (64 hex chars). SHA256 is only accepted when SMS is disabled in the SMS+ template.
                + `pnp` (required, object) - LINE Notification Message setting
                    + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Notification Message template: name vs. value
                    + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the LINE Notification Message template: name vs. value
                + `sms` (required, object) - SMS setting
                    + `PARAM_1` (optional, string) - parameter in the SMS template: name vs. value
                    + `PARAM_2` (optional, string) - parameter in the SMS template: name vs. value
                + `customized_id` (optional, string) - A user-defined ID for tracking or correlating messages across systems.

    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

    + Body

            {
                "pnp_setting_id": 1111,
                "event_id": 123,
                "data": [
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                        "pnp": {
                            "days": "7",
                            "location_name": "A store",
                            "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                            "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                            "order_url": "http://maac.io/xxxxx"
                        },
                        "sms": {
                            "order_number": "AJ1234567",
                            "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                            "location_name": "A store",
                            "days": "7"
                        },
                        "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                    },
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345679",
                        "pnp": {
                            "days": "7",
                            "location_name": "B store",
                            "order_number": "BK7654321",
                            "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                            "order_url": "http://maac.io/xxxxx"
                        },
                        "sms": {
                            "order_number": "BK7654321",
                            "arrival_date": "2020/7/30",
                            "location_name": "B store",
                            "days": "7"
                        },
                        "customized_id": "BK7654321890"
                    }
                ]
            }

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (array)
        + (object)
            + `id` (number) - SMS+ message ID
            + `result` (string)
              SMS+ message status
                + `pending` - We are processing this message

    + Body

            [
                {
                  "id": 1111,
                  "result": "pending"
                },
                {
                  "id": 1112,
                  "result": "pending"
                }
            ]

+ Response 400 (text/plain)
    - `pnp setting not found` - SMS+ campaign ID is invalid
    - `field is required` - Missing required field in LINE Notification Message or SMS setting
    - `this value does not match the required pattern` - The phone number format is invalid
    - `your SMS points are insufficient, please recharge before sending` - You don't have enough MAAC points; please contact us

    + Body

            pnp setting not found

+ Response 403 (text/plain)
    - `You do not have permission to perform this action` - The authorization token is invalid

    + Body

            You do not have permission to perform this action

### Get Sending Records List  [GET /openapi/v1/pnp/message/{?pnp_setting_id,updated_at_min,updated_at_max,start}]

After sending a SMS+ message, you can get its sending record. This API can be used to track the status change of sending records.
The list is paged for every 300 tags, and the result data is ordered by `updated_at` descend.

> Filter with a time range (from `updated_at_min` to `updated_at_max`) to get the records that were updated during this time period.

+ **Notes**
+ We only accept ISO 8601 datetime format in `updated_at_min` and `updated_at_max`.
+ Please encode the `+` character in the datetime string (the URL encoded result of `+` is `%2B`). If not, the response will be a `400` format error.
+ If the datetime string does not contain a timezone, we will use this as the timezone of `Asia/Taipei`.

+ Request (application/json)
    + Headers

            Authorization: Bearer {Access token}

+ Parameters
    + pnp_setting_id (required, number) - SMS+ campaign ID
    + updated_at_min : `2022-10-13T16:03:15.248652%2B08:00` (required, string) - date time string that `updated_at` query range starts at (ISO 8601)
    + updated_at_max : `2022-10-18T16:03:15.248652%2B08:00` (required, string) - date time string that `updated_at` query range ends at (ISO 8601)
    + customized_id (optional, string) - A user-defined ID.
    + start : `OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D`(optional, string) -
    The cursor of the next page. It will be returned in the `next` parameter of the previous page.

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    + Attributes (object)
        + `results` (array) - array of sending records
            + (object)
                + `pnp_message_id` (number) - ID of sending record. Corresponding to the `id` in the response of "Send single LINE SMS+ message" API
                + `phone_number` (string) -  The mobile phone number of the user.
                + `status` (enum) - The final status of this sending record.
                    + line_push_preparing - Start LINE Push sending process.
                    + line_push_delivered - The LINE Push Message has been delivered to the user.
                    + line_push_failed - The LINE Push Message failed to send.
                    + line_push_undeliverable - The LINE push message cannot be delivered (e.g., reach monthly limit, inactive customers, Line API timeout).
                    + pnp_preparing - start LINE notification message sending process.
                    + pnp_accepted - LINE accepted LINE notification message send request
                    + pnp_delivered - LINE notification message has been delivered to the user
                    + pnp_failed - LINE notification message failed to send
                    + pnp_undeliverable - LINE notification message cannot be delivered (e.g., blocked LINE OA)
                    + sms_preparing - start SMS message sending process.
                    + sms_accepted - SMS provider accepted SMS send request
                    + sms_delivered - SMS has been delivered to the user
                    + sms_failed - SMS failed to send
                    + sms_undeliverable - SMS cannot be delivered(ex: Poor signal, shutdown)
                    + sms_blocked - The SMS was blocked because the phone number was in the blocked list
                    + sms_temporary_error - The SMS vendor is temporarily broken. MAAC will retry sending until the end of the retry time period. If all retries are failed, this status would be changed to `sms_failed`.
                    + sms_callback_timeout - MAAC did not receive SMS vendor's response within timeout period.
                + `line_push_template_id` (number, nullable) - LINE Message Template ID.
                + `line_push_status` (string, nullable) - Process status of LINE Push Message.
                + `line_push_delivered_at` (string, nullable) - Delivery time of LINE Push Message (ISO 8601).
                + `line_push_error_category` (enum, nullable) - The error category of the Line Push message.
                    + member_not_found - The Line push cannot be delivered because we can’t locate only one active contact in MAAC.(e.g. user block LINE OA, find more than 1 contact with the receiver phone number.)
                    + reach_monthly_limit - The Line push cannot be delivered because you have reached the Line msg month limit.
                    + others - Other errors.
                + `pnp_status` (string, nullable) - Process status of LINE Notification Message.
                + `pnp_delivered_at` (string, nullable) - Delivery time of a LINE Notification Message (ISO 8601).
                + `sms_status` (string, nullable) - Process status of SMS Message.
                + `sms_delivered_at` (string, nullable) - Sending time of a SMS message (ISO 8601)
                + `sms_error_category` (enum, nullable) - The error category of the SMS message.
                    + target_reception_issue - The SMS cannot be delivered due to telecom or reception issue (e.g., target is offline, base station has issue)
                    + invalid_phone_number - The phone number is invalid or does not exist.
                    + sensitive_words - The message contains sensitive words.
                    + others - Other errors
                + `updated_at` (string) - The update time of this sending record (ISO 8601)
                + `event_id` (number) - message event ID
                + `customized_id` (string, nullable) - A user-defined ID.
        + `next` (string) - page token of the next page

    + Body

            {
                "next": "OwNdFUXTfIyunwhn55vJh4fE0wu13wSPRTCUiaqhN1Nu0vLXHpzatVFtb9ZYKBxwGKoy3jOfvxSzEfOOZnFz5Y%2BKcvexmL39l5xQqQSwtiA%3D",
                "results": [
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                        "pnp_message_id": 5,
                        "status": "line_push_delivered",
                        "line_push_template_id": 1,
                        "line_push_status": "line_push_delivered",
                        "line_push_delivered_at": "2022-10-14T10:33:41.343356+08:00",
                        "line_push_error_category": null,
                        "pnp_status": null,
                        "pnp_delivered_at": null,
                        "sms_status": null,
                        "sms_delivered_at": null,
                        "sms_error_category": null,
                        "updated_at": "2022-10-14T10:33:41.343356+08:00",
                        "event_id": 123,
                        "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                    },
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                        "pnp_message_id": 4,
                        "status": "pnp_preparing",
                        "line_push_template_id": null,
                        "line_push_status": null,
                        "line_push_delivered_at": null,
                        "line_push_error_category": null,
                        "pnp_status": "pnp_preparing",
                        "pnp_delivered_at": null,
                        "sms_status": null,
                        "sms_delivered_at": null,
                        "sms_error_category": null,
                        "updated_at": "2022-10-14T10:33:41.343356+08:00",
                        "event_id": 123,
                        "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                    },
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                        "pnp_message_id": 3,
                        "status": "pnp_delivered",
                        "line_push_template_id": null,
                        "line_push_status": null,
                        "line_push_delivered_at": null,
                        "line_push_error_category": null,
                        "pnp_status": "pnp_delivered",
                        "pnp_delivered_at": "2022-10-13T16:39:15.248652+08:00",
                        "sms_status": null,
                        "sms_delivered_at": null,
                        "sms_error_category": null,
                        "updated_at": "2022-10-13T16:39:15.248652+08:00",
                        "event_id": 123,
                        "customized_id": "AJ1234567890"
                    },
                    {
                        "phone_number": "+886912345678",
                        "pnp_message_id": 2,
                        "status": "sms_delivered",
                        "line_push_template_id": null,
                        "line_push_status": null,
                        "line_push_delivered_at": null,
